CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 10, 1958, pg. 24 reads: "All Yours - Dr. James Stewart, Polemarch of the Pittsburgh Alumni Chapter of Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity, presents Pitt basketball, star Julius Pegues, his class ring during a testimonial banquet held in his honor last week. Looking on, left to right, are the Rev. S. Amos Brackeen, sports announcer, Ray Scott; Capt. Tom Hamilton, Pitt athletic director, and Bob Timmons, Pitt cage coach. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of six members of Kappa Alpha Psi:  Rev. S. Amos Brackeen, Ray Scott, Dr. James Stewart presenting class ring to Pitt basketball star Julius Pegues, Capt. Tom Hamilton, and Bob Timmons, standing in wood paneled interior with bare tree patterned curtains and leaf and lattice patterned carpeting, during testimonial banquet
